e unrestricted, directed toward a specific endowment or project and are tax-deductible. The Office of Development will be glad to assist you with any questions regarding making a gift to the College. The College of Music is grateful to our many friends and supporters who help us sustain our reputation as one of the best music schools in the nation. To make a gift: Make a gift online Contact the College of Music Office of Development Contact the UNT Office of Development Ways to Give Many gift options are available. Whether you are considering one for immediate use or a legacy gift, all are important and make a difference. Join the Dean’s Camerata Scholarship Program Sponsor an annual scholarship for a music student at the $1000 level. Find out more>> Create an Endowment An endowed gift provides support in perpetuity through scholarships, fellowships, professorships and chairs. The minimum endowed scholarship level is $25,000.Find out more>> Support the Dean’s Discretionary Fund The Dean’s Discretionary Fund provides the opportunity to support the mission of the College in such varied ways as travel, scholarships, recordings, publicity and outreach. Contact the Development Office for more details. Naming Opportunities There are many naming opportunities within the College of Music. Donors may achieve permanent recognition or honor loved ones by naming a space within a music building on campus. The space can be a lobby, balcony, rehearsal hall, classroom or building. The minimum naming amounts depend upon the size and location of the space. Contact the Development Office for more details. Planned Gifts and Stocks Contact the College of Music Development Office for more information about planned gifts and stocks. Visit Us Music Building 415 Avenue C Denton, TX 76201 Mail Us University of North Texas 1155 Union Circle #311367 Denton, TX 76203-5017 Contact Us 940-565-2791 music.information@unt.edu Technical issues? Site last updated on May 09, 2017 Disclaimer| AA/EOE/ADA